# NSHostingView overlay click-through prevention

SwiftUI views hosted in NSHostingView overlays (file previews, code blocks, etc.) must have `.contentShape(Rectangle())` on their root container to prevent mouse events from passing through to the NSTextView underneath.

**Why:** On 2026-04-02, clicking anywhere inside the file preview panel (not just on buttons) opened the file in an external app. SwiftUI only registers hit targets on visible content (text, images, buttons). Empty areas within the glass container had no hit target, so clicks fell through the NSHostingView to the NSTextView, which interpreted them as clicks on the attachment character and triggered the default open-file behavior.

**How to apply:** Any SwiftUI view that fills an NSHostingView overlay over the text editor should include `.contentShape(Rectangle())` before its background modifier. This makes the entire rect a hit target, consuming mouse events that would otherwise pass through.

```swift
VStack { ... }
    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)
    .contentShape(Rectangle())  // Prevent click-through
    .thinLiquidGlass(in: ...)
```
